      "date": "2018-10-28 10:04:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2\n\nIn general, it might be better to avoid the lprocfs files, since James is modifying them fairly frequently, and it is better IMHO to update the nearby whitespace as part of a patch that has to odifyvthe code anyway, but since this patch is here we may as well land it if it doesn't conflict with anything. \n\nNote that you can pre-check for potentially conflicting patches before working on a file by searching for \"file:filename is:open\" in the search box. I wouldn't worry about ancient patches, but no point in pushing a patch that conflicts with an active patch (say < 2 months old) if there are other files that might be cleaned up.",
